<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_JungleAdventure_Archaeology_Skill" s="181493">
  <T n="category">181477<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_Jungle_Adventure--></T>
  <T n="name">0xFBC04CD2<!--String: "Archaeology "--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Archaeology_Skill_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d3278c4773eae4cb</T>
      <T n="text">0x1C906EA0<!--String: "Sims who love history and love digging in the dirt find a fortunate confluence of these passions in Archaeology. This skill will reward you with knowledge, and fabulous artifacts to decorate the house."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Archaeology_Skill_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d3278c4773eae4c8</T>
      <T n="text">0x5A9AD23D<!--String: "Sims can stick their heads in a skill book or they can head out into the field to learn Archaeology.\n\nIn the Belomisia Jungle, Excavate Dig Piles or Excavation Sites to increase skill. The archaeology work bench can be used to Uncover and Authenticate found artifacts. Sims with a high level skill may also receive requests from the Archeology Institute to authenticate artifacts. Sims need to remember to return those objects to collect a service fee."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Archaeology_Skill_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d3278c4773eae4c9</T>
      <T n="text">0xEEC6C634<!--String: "Dig piles and Excavation Sites will have a number of different items to be found. Expect to find clumps of dirt, Unauthenticated artifacts, fossils, bone dust and more.\n\nClumps of Dirt may look unexciting, but with the help of a archaeology work bench a Sim can find the artifact within.\n\nIf you find bone dust make sure to keep it. Bone dust can be traded to Selvadoradians for powerful poison antidotes."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Archaeology_Skill_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d3278c4773eae4ce</T>
      <T n="text">0x73F8E137<!--String: "One of the perks of the Archaeology Skill is the ability of upgrading dig piles to excavation sites.  Excavation sites allow up to four Sims to dig at once. These sites also allow archaeologists to dig up more artifacts than a standard dig pile.\n\nWith a Level 6 or higher archaeologist, click on a dig pile and choose 'Establish Excavation Site'."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Archaeology_Skill_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d3278c4773eae4cf</T>
      <T n="text">0x8167A614<!--String: "Every Archaeologist needs a dependable Archaeology Work Bench to work on. This handy work bench allows a Sim Uncover Artifacts from clumps of dirt. They then can Authenticate those artifacts to determine their rarity.\n\nWhen an artifact is fully authenticated the Sim can still Analyze the collectible for fun and archaeology skill!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">6</T>
</I>